{{Distinguish|Local education authority}}
'''Local education agency''' ('''LEA''') is a commonly used acronym for a [[school district]], an entity which operates local public primary and secondary schools in the [[United States]], or provides government services to schools within a local area in the [[United Kingdom]].<ref>[http://www.northumberlandlea.net/ Northumberland LEA website], Northumberland County Council 2006 - 2009.  Accessed 2009-06-04.</ref>

In some instances, LEA is used to refer to an individual school, especially a charter school, though this usage is less common.

